Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place in a #large bowl{}. Add half
the @soy sauce{4%tablespoon} and half the @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters} (you'll use
the rest later). Turn to coat. Set aside to marinate, skin sides up, at least
~{10%minutes}.

> Barramundi is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.

Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Zucchini ==

While rice cooks, trim and halve @zucchini{1%ounce} lengthwise; cut crosswise into
1/2-inch-thick half-moons. Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and slice lengthwise into
1/4-inch-thick planks; stack planks and slice lengthwise to create
1/4-inch-thick matchsticks. Trim and halve @scallions{2} lengthwise; cut crosswise
into 1-inch pieces, separating whites from greens. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Soy Ginger Sauce ==

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together remaining soy sauce, remaining ponzu, 2 TBSP
warm water, and 1 tsp @sugar{1%tsp} until sugar dissolves.

== Steaming ==

Cut a 12-inch-long piece of @aluminum foil{1%piece}. Roll up foil lengthwise, then
form into a coil.

Place foil coil in center of a #large pan{}. Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on
top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and lightly browned,
~{14-16%minutes}.

While zucchini cooks, place barramundi, skin sides down, on a #heatproof plate{};
discard any remaining marinade.

> We used an 8-inch dinner plate (the plate should be slightly smaller than the pan).

Set #plate{} with barramundi on top of foil coil, gently pressing plate so it's level
and foil flattens slightly. Carefully fill bottom of pan with 1 inch of water.

> Re-center plate and foil in pan if needed.

Cover pan with a tight-fitting #lid{} and heat over high heat until water boils. Reduce
heat to medium; steam, covered, until fish is cooked through and easily flakes with
a #fork{}, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Carefully transfer fish to a separate #plate{}.

== Sauce ==

While fish steams, heat @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #small pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add ginger and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant and scallion
whites are lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in scallion greens and half the cilantro. Add soy sauce mixture and cook,
stirring, until sauce has reduced slightly, ~{30-60%seconds}.

== To Serve ==

Divide rice and roasted zucchini between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections; top
rice with barramundi.

> If you prefer to remove the skin, turn fish skin side up and gently pull skin away using a fork.

Spoon sauce over barramundi and garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve.